---
import ArticleLayout from "../../components/ArticleLayout.astro";

const title = "Longevity: Treating Aging Like an Engineering Problem — Future";
const updated = "Updated: 2026";
---

<ArticleLayout title={title}>
  <article class="page">
    <header class="hero">
      <div class="hero-top">
        <a class="back" href="/">← Back to Atlas</a>
        <span class="chip chip--topic">BIOTECH</span>
      </div>

      <h1>Longevity: Treating Aging Like an Engineering Problem</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">The big shift is prevention: measure the body continuously, catch problems early, and repair damage before it becomes disease.</p>

      <div class="hero-grid">
        <section class="card card--soft">
          <h2 class="hsmall">What you’ll learn</h2>
          <ul class="list">
            <li>Why “aging” is a bundle of processes, not one switch.</li>
            <li>What's real today: <b>screening</b>, <b>risk reduction</b>, and better diagnostics.</li>
            <li>What's experimental: <b>senolytics</b>, <b>gene therapies</b>, and regeneration.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="card card--ink">
          <p class="quote">“Longevity isn't one miracle pill — it's a boring system: measurement, maintenance, and repair.”</p>
          <p class="meta">{updated}</p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>TL;DR</h2>
      <div class="tldr">
        <div class="tldr-item">
          <div class="dot dot--a" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <div>
            <h3>Most gains are prevention</h3>
            <p>Blood pressure, lipids, glucose, sleep, fitness, and screenings still dominate outcomes.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tldr-item">
          <div class="dot dot--b" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <div>
            <h3>Diagnostics compound</h3>
            <p>Cheaper sequencing + better biomarkers = earlier detection and better targeting.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tldr-item">
          <div class="dot dot--c" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <div>
            <h3>Repair is the frontier</h3>
            <p>Cell cleanup, immune tuning, and regeneration are promising — but slow to prove.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>What “aging as engineering” means</h2>
      <p class="lead">Aging is accumulated damage: DNA errors, misfolded proteins, worn mitochondria, chronic inflammation, and senescent “zombie” cells. The goal is to <b>measure</b> damage and <b>reduce</b> or <b>repair</b> it.</p>
      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="hsmall">Three layers</h3>
          <div class="stack">
            <div class="callout"><h4>Monitoring</h4><p>Better biomarkers, imaging, and wearables to see risk earlier.</p></div>
            <div class="callout"><h4>Prevention</h4><p>Lowering failure probability: cardio-metabolic health, strength, sleep.</p></div>
            <div class="callout"><h4>Repair</h4><p>Removing damage (senescent cells), restoring function, tuning immune response.</p></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="hsmall">Realistic now</h3>
          <ul class="list">
            <li><b>Risk factors:</b> BP, ApoB/LDL, glucose, body composition, fitness.</li>
            <li><b>Screening:</b> evidence-based schedules and trend tracking.</li>
            <li><b>Habits:</b> strength + zone-2 cardio, sleep consistency, low smoking.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>What's coming (likely)</h2>
      <p class="lead">Expect gradual gains: better detection and targeted therapies for narrow conditions first.</p>
      <div class="card"><div class="grid3">
          <div class="mini"><h4>Biomarkers</h4><p>Blood signals for inflammation, organ stress, and early tumor detection.</p></div>
          <div class="mini"><h4>Personalized plans</h4><p>Interventions tailored to risk profiles and measurable response.</p></div>
          <div class="mini"><h4>Targeted therapies</h4><p>More precise drugs and gene therapies, scaling over time.</p></div>
        </div></div>
        <p class="note">The limiting factor is evidence: humans live long, so trials take time and money.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>FAQ</h2>
      <div class="faq">
        <details><summary>Will we ‘cure aging’ soon?</summary><p>Not as a single event. Expect incremental improvements and targeted repairs for specific problems first.</p></details>
        <details><summary>What's the most underrated lever?</summary><p>Maintaining muscle and cardio fitness — it protects metabolism, mobility, and resilience.</p></details>
      </div>
    </section>

    <nav class="footnav" aria-label="Next and previous">
      <a class="btn btn--ghost" href="/future/ai-agents">← Prev: AI Agents</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/future/space-economy">Next: Space Economy →</a>
    </nav>
  </article>

</ArticleLayout>
